        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 2:52PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 252 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Texas Creek, or 48 miles southwest of Colorado Springs, moving south
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, penny size hail and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texas Creek and Hillside.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
